ronunciations of <i>Henry</i> (see   Harry  ).","History: Harrison is an extremely common surname in northern England. One important and influential American family of bearers are descended from Benjamin Harrison, who emigrated from England to VA in 1633 or 1634. Descendants include another Benjamin Harrison (<i>c.</i> 1726–91), who was an activist in the American Revolution and a signer of the Declaration of Independence. His son William Henry Harrison (1773–1841) and great-grandson Benjamin Harrison (1833–1901) both became presidents of the US."],"variants":[{"name":"Harry","meanings":["English (mainly south Wales and southwestern England): from the medieval personal name <i>Harry</i>, a common form of   Henry  , with assimilation of <i>-nr-</i> to <i>-rr-</i> and regular Middle English change of <i>-er-</i> to <i>-ar-</i>. In south Wales the surname is generally a post-medieval coinage, in most cases not hereditary until the 18th or 19th century.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Hariric</i>, composed of the elements <i>hari</i>, <i>heri</i> ‘army’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power(ful)’.","Native American (e.g. Navajo): adoption of the English personal name <i>Harry</i> (see 1 above) as a surname."]},{"name":"Arrizon","meanings":["Hispanic (mainly Mexico): probably an altered form of English   Harrison  ."]},{"name":"Harison","meanings":["English: variant of   Harrison  ."]},{"name":"Arrison","meanings":["English: variant of   Harrison  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":49,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"John Harrison was born about 1500, in Waltham Abbey, Essex, England. He married Agnes about 1524, in Waltham Abbey, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 3 daughters. He died before 28 April 1551, in Waltham Abbey, Essex, England, and was buried in Waltham Holy Cross, Essex, England."},"et":{"about 1500–before 28 April 1551":"umbes 1500–enne 28. aprilli 1551","1500–1582":"1500–1582","1515–1597":"1515–1597","1525–1601":"1525–1601","1528–1576":"1528–1576","1536–1581":"1536–1581","1500–1551":"1500–1551","30 December 1515":"30. detsember 1515","1582":"1582","1581":"1581","1525":"1525","4 January 1550":"4. jaanuar 1550","1536":"1536","1601":"1601","1522":"1522","1500":"1500","about 1536":"umbes 1536","1576":"1576","1597":"1597","about 1524":"umbes 1524","1551":"1551","about 1500":"umbes 1500","from 1500 to 1551":"1500 kuni 1551","1528":"1528","1549":"1549","before 28 April 1551":"enne 28. aprilli 1551","1515":"1515","Waltham Holy Cross, Essex, England":"Waltham Holy Cross, Essex, England","Waltham Abbey, Essex, England":"Waltham Abbey, Essex, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1500–before 28 April 1551":"noin 1500–ennen vuotta 28. huhtikuuta 1551","1500–1582":"1500–1582","1515–1597":"1515–1597","1525–1601":"1525–1601","1528–1576":"1528–1576","1536–1581":"1536–1581","1500–1551":"1500–1551","30 December 1515":"30. joulukuuta 1515","1582":"1582","1581":"1581","1525":"1525","4 January 1550":"4. tammikuuta 1550","1536":"1536","1601":"1601","1522":"1522","1500":"1500","about 1536":"noin 1536","1576":"1576","1597":"1597","about 1524":"noin 1524","1551":"1551","about 1500":"noin 1500","from 1500 to 1551":"vuodesta 1500 vuoteen 15